{
  "text": "(a) implies s = r which is a contradiction. (b) implies that sw = ws which contredicts (\u22c6). Finally (c) implies w =\u0175rsr (with\u0175 defined in A1). Considering \u2113(w) and the reduction condition (see [CITATION_1] , Theorem 1.2.5), one must delete two generators on the expression\u0175rsr to obtain a reduced expression of w. Hence, observe that there is s or r at the right end of a reduced expression of w. Therefore, r \u2208 D(w) or s \u2208 D(w) which contredicts hypothesis or r \u2208 D(w). Hence r \u2208 D(sw) hence r \u2208 D(w).",
